It is being said that the dead belonged to the police as well as the frontier core.
Eye witnesses say that a letter was also found near the bodies. It warns that whoever moved these bodies before 11:00 am, would be responsible for his own death.
Locals are saying that the two bodies were left in the marketplace until 11:00, after which security officers carried both bodies to the hospital.
A dangerous increase in the number of target killing over the last few weeks has been seen in the central and surrounding areas of Mengorah
Civilians, including women as well as security officers were killed.
According to local sources, until now, more than thirty people were killed in such incidents.
No organization has accepted responsibility for these deaths yet.
