Victory of a British hacker in the court.
A 42-year-old British citizen has admitted that he hacked an American military website.
Gary has Asperger's syndrome. It should be kept in mind that an Asperger's patient has the obsession to do similar kinds of tasks.
His lawyers say that if he is handed over to America then he will commit suicide.
However, government officials say that they are no threat to Gary's health.
Lord justice Morskey and Mr. Justice Simon while announcing the decision said that Gary is permitted to file a review petition in a British court.

He added that the secretary of interior has noticed this issue.
But the government prosecutors say that the secretary of interior had used his authority.
Gary has never denied hacking the American military website.
In 2001 and 2002, Gary hacked an American computer system which caused a loss to the American government of eight hundred thousand dollars.
Gary hacked 97 computers including those of the American Navy and NASA.
However, Gary says that he did not do this with bad intentions, as he was just looking for information about aliens, which he thought the American government had kept secret.
Gary's mother, Janice Sharp, has said that she is happy with this decision.
Gary's lawyer has said that it is the right decision.
This case has continued since 2002, and finally a correct decision has been made.
Kashmir: Two Hizb Commanders killed.
Colonel Acharya, spokesman of the northern command of the Indian Army deployed in Jammu, told BBC, based on reliable information, that troops from twenty-four Rashtria rifles and Jammu Kashmir police besieged the place in Batihaas jungle within Tehsil Gandwa of the Doda district, where the armed extremists were hiding.
They fired at the army, and in retaliation, two extremists were killed.
The spokesman said that one of the two killed extremists is district commander Zahoor-ud-din of prohibited Hizbul Mujahiddins, who was active for 12 years in the district and was an expert in gunpowder explosives.
His partner has been identified as Sajjad Hussain who, according to Army, was connected with extremists from last year.
According to Acharia, the operation still continues in the mentioned jungle areas because, according to them, there is more possibility that there are more extremists there. Army says that two rifles were recovered in the first phase of the operation.
