Most of the elders in our family belonged to the working class.
During our childhood when our uncles did their work, we prayed to Allah to protect us from physical labor.
To avoid this we wrote to the editor of monthly Amroz to ask him what to do after matriculation so that we would not have to do physical labor.
In reply, the Editor wrote that we should become a Doctor or Engineer and study these courses.
We were inclined towards engineering and in matriculation we studied Technical drawing instead of Biology.
But at the time of admissions in FSc, our older brother forced us to study medical in FSc.
We had hardly studied biology for a month before we started studying math.
In order to avoid physical labor, we became engineers and we are in a better position than many friends in our family. We thank Allah for it.
We remembered this when with out 2 young sons we were trying to lift carpets of old hour.
It was only half an hour since he started working that the little boy said, "Daddy, I am not born to do this".
I said that if this is true, then study a lot like us and get rid of the physical labor.
The son said, "I am studying and I will get through it, but it is the work that I cannot do".
We did that work in three hours and came back home.
The point of this story is that if a person picks his destiny, whatever is the reason behind it, no one can stop him from achieving that destiny.
Here if you do not know what you have to do then may God help you!
